The relations between the concentration of Cr(VI)/VB12 and the fluorescence quenching efficiency of CDs-Ws-Amp Na were studied. With the increase of Cr(VI)/VB12 concentrations, the fluorescence intensity of CDs-Ws-Amp Na decreases (Figs. S14a–14d). The ratio of fluorescence intensity of CDs-Ws-Amp Na is linear with Cr(VI) at the concentration of 0–50 μM (R2 = 0.9930) Fig. S14e with LOD 106.57 nM (Fig. S14e); and linear with VB12 concentration at 0–25 μM (R2 = 0.9945) with LOD 51.50 nM (Fig. S14f) (Table 1
                         and Table 2
                        ). The signal-noise (S/N) ratio is three. Thus, Amp Na detection could be used as signal-on, and detection for Cr(VI) and VB12 could be performed based on signal-off.
